<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Typography Example</title>
  <style>
    h1 {
      font-family: "Arial", sans-serif;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-style: italic;
      font-weight: normal;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    p {
      line-height: 1.8;
      text-align: justify;
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: lighter;
      margin: 15px;
    }

    a {
      text-decoration: none;
      color: blue;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Main Heading with Custom Font and Spacing</h1>

  <h2>Subheading with Italic Font Style</h2>

  <p>
    This is a sample paragraph to demonstrate <strong>typography in CSS</strong>. 
    Notice that the text is justified, making both edges aligned neatly. 
    The <span style="font-weight: normal;">normal weight</span>, 
    <span style="font-weight: bold;">bold weight</span>, and 
    <span style="font-weight: lighter;">lighter weight</span> 
    are shown here for comparison.
  </p>

  

